<subSubSection id="C2DF6529F335FFFBFF15FA02FDD061CC" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8A7A36A2F335FFFBFF15FA02FDD061CC" blockId="12.[192,1440,1467,1524]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="B8B1EAB0F335FFFBFF15FA02FEC261EC" bold="true" box="[192,347,1467,1491]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is named for the Parque Nacional Natural Gorgona in 
<collectingCountry id="F2D27632F335FFFBFB77FA02FA8061EC" box="[1186,1305,1467,1491]" name="Colombia" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, where the two female 
<typeStatus id="557E8800F335FFFBFE98FA65FE1761CB" box="[333,398,1500,1524]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">types</typeStatus>
were collected.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C2DF6529F335FFFBFF15F9B2FCEA62BA" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8A7A36A2F335FFFBFF15F9B2FCEA62BA" blockId="12.[192,1441,1547,1669]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="B8B1EAB0F335FFFBFF15F9B2FED6621C" bold="true" box="[192,335,1547,1571]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4DC54D21F335FFFBFE83F9B2FD90621C" authorityName="Flowers" authorityYear="2018" box="[342,521,1547,1571]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Beltia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gorgona">
<emphasis id="B8B1EAB0F335FFFBFE83F9B2FD90621C" box="[342,521,1547,1571]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Beltia gorgona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from other species in the genus by its larger size and brilliant dark green color with purple reflexions (which are easily seen with the naked eye but very difficult to photograph). It differs from 
<emphasis id="B8B1EAB0F335FFFBFD79F9F4FC23625B" box="[684,954,1613,1636]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">
<taxonomicName id="4DC54D21F335FFFBFD79F9F4FC2C625B" authorityName="Flowers" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Bechyne" baseAuthorityYear="2018" box="[684,949,1613,1636]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Beltia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angustomarginata">B. angustomarginata</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
another species with a marked purple reflexions, by the less transverse shape of the pronotum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C2DF6529F335FFFBFF15F927FD0B6307" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8A7A36A2F335FFFBFF15F927FD0B6307" blockId="12.[192,1440,1694,1848]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="B8B1EAB0F335FFFBFF15F927FEDA6289" bold="true" box="[192,323,1694,1718]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Remarks.</emphasis>
Two male specimens in poor condition, labeled simply “South America, 
<collectingCountry id="F2D27632F335FFFBFB19F927FAA66289" box="[1228,1343,1694,1718]" name="Colombia" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Colombia</collectingCountry>
/feeding on banana leaves” (FSCA), are tentatively assigned to this species but not included in the type series. They differ from the 
<typeStatus id="557E8800F335FFFBFE69F966FDBD62C8" box="[444,548,1759,1783]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">holotype</typeStatus>
in having a stronger coppery color and a sharper and more asymmetrical tip on the median lobe of the aedeagus. The type series of 
<taxonomicName id="4DC54D21F335FFFBFC56F8B9FB9F6328" authorityName="Flowers" authorityYear="2018" box="[899,1030,1792,1815]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Beltia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gorgona">
<emphasis id="B8B1EAB0F335FFFBFC56F8B9FB9F6328" box="[899,1030,1792,1815]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">B. gorgona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comes from only two localities on the Pacific coast of 
<collectingCountry id="F2D27632F335FFFBFE7FF899FD846307" box="[426,541,1824,1848]" name="Colombia" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Colombia</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="12FE2A27F335FFFBFDFBF899FD1C6307" box="[558,645,1824,1848]" captionStart="Figures 78–79" captionStartId="43.[191,286,1850,1872]" captionTargetBox="[192,1441,412,1699]" captionTargetId="figure@43.[189,1443,412,1702]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="Figures 78–79. Distribution maps for Beltia spp. 78) Northwestern South America: B. confusa (star), B. gorgona (inverted triangles), B. placidula (blue circles), B. rugosa (red circle), B. weyrauchi (square). 79) Ecuador: B. awapita (hexagon), B. ledesmae (squares), B. napoensis (triangles), B. talaga (circle), B. tsachila (star)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3713527" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3713527/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Fig. 78</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
